        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Together, Rush Limbaugh, Roger Ailes and Rupert Murdoch challenged the old guard's dominance by developing viable conservative alternatives in every medium. Limbaugh, a charismatic radio veteran, took his show national in 1988 and drew a weekly audience of some 20m listeners by the 1990s. He also published »",
